OL,3,C'Scrabble' romance scammer conned
OL,4,Celderly pensioner out of #20,000
OL,6,FOn another occasion, the fraudster
OL,7,Fclaimed he needed to pay a bail fee
OL,8,Fafter being arrested in Turkey while
OL,9,Freturning from a business trip. He
OL,10,Feven emailed a fake letter, from the
OL,11,FUnited Nations, stating that he was a
OL,12,Fprisoner.
OL,14,FThe fraud was only uncovered, after 18
OL,15,Fmonths, when the woman's suspicions
OL,16,Fwere raised and she told her brother.
OL,17,FHe reported it to the authorities.
